<p>If you've searched for <strong>Little Boracay</strong> and wondered whether it's the same as the famous <strong>Boracay Island in Aklan</strong> — they are completely different destinations. Here's a full comparison to help you choose.</p>

<h2>The Quick Answer</h2>
<p><strong>Little Boracay</strong> is a natural tidal sandbar in <strong>Calatagan, Batangas</strong> — reachable by a 3–4 hour drive from Manila, no flight needed. <strong>Boracay Island</strong> is a developed island resort destination in <strong>Malay, Aklan</strong> — requiring a flight and ferry, typically a 2–3 night trip.</p>

