<h2>Which One Should You Visit?</h2>
<p><strong>Choose Little Boracay</strong> if you want a quick, affordable coastal escape from Manila — a day trip with friends or family on a floating cottage over a natural sandbar, without the cost and logistics of a flight.</p>
<p><strong>Choose Boracay Island</strong> if you're planning a multi-day beach holiday, want full resort amenities, nightlife, and don't mind the travel and cost.</p>
<p>The good news? They're not mutually exclusive — visit Little Boracay for a weekend day trip, and save Boracay Island for your next big holiday.</p>

